On the other hand the same cause sometimes gives rise to
apparently needless variations, such as ἄρχεις .. κρατεῖς, Ο. Τ. 54;
δεδοικας.. ταρβεῖς, Τr. 457.

ὁδός, first signifying a road, acquires the general meaning of a way. It is applied in the special meanings of an enterprize,
El. 1295; the trouble of going for something, O. T. 1478;
a plan or device (metaph.), O. T. 67; conduct, Ant. 1274; the road of death, Tr. 875.
